articles.title: The future is uncertain for the U.S. after crashing out of the Women's World Cup - NPR
articles.description: The once-dominant Americans crashed out of the World Cup on penalties after a scoreless draw with Sweden in the Round of 16. It was the earliest exit ever for the four-time tournament champions.
articles.content:
U.S. players react following their loss to Sweden in a penalty shootout during the Women's World Cup round of 16 soccer match in Melbourne, Australia, Sunday, Aug. 6, 2023.
Scott Barbour/AP
